During Mr Kenei’s burial in Rongai, Nakuru, DP Ruto pledged to the family that he would make sure the killers were found.Ten months have since passed and little has been heard about the progress of finding Mr Kenei’s killers. When former Sports Cabinet Secretary Rashid Echesa was arrested over a fake arms deal, it was impossible at that time to predict that the saga would lead to a murder that almost changed Kenya’s political landscape. 

Yet it did. That Mr Echesa, a Standard Seven dropout who transformed himself into a shrewd political mobiliser, earning himself a cabinet slot has always been controversial inside and outside government, is not in question. 



