The answers, perhaps, lie in the identity of three strangers who were the last people to visit Sergeant Kenei’s house on the day he was murdered.  Five months later, police yet to unravel the mystery murder of the officer who was head of security at DP Ruto’s office. This comes months after he was arrested amid a probe into his role in a Sh39 billion fake tender deal. The DP's ambition to take over from his boss after the 2022 elections is a road with two paths. The decision is a blow to two aspirants who had applied to the party for sponsorship to contest the seat. This shift of focus is so dire that the World Health Organization now warns that by the end of 2020, more people will have died of malaria than Covid-19.